We are pleased to advise you that your application to Eve College has been accepted and you are offered a place for the following course:
Certificate IV in Entrepreneurship and New Business
NOTE: All fees are subject to variation and may change without notice.
BSB40320 Certificate IV in Entrepreneurship and New Business (7 academic weeks and 3 weeks
The minimum amount of full-time study is 20 contact hours per week which consist of 14 hours of face to face
and 6 hours of self-paced distance learning per week.
This offer is only valid upon successful achievement on these condition(s):
Students are required to be at least 18 years of age at the time of course commencement
Students are required to have an English level at least IELTS 5.5 (or equivalent)
Students are required to have completed year 12 (or equivalent) or pass the Language/ Literacy/ Numeracy test
Students who cannot provide both a minimum of a year 12 (or equivalent) and an English Certificate of IELTS 5.5 (or equivalent), or an
AQF Certificate IV (or higher) to the level specified for the course will be required to undertake LLN testing prior to receiving an offer.
These students must achieve at minimum:
For Certificate IV (Learning 2; Reading 3; Writing 3; Oral Communication 2; Numeracy 2)
For Diploma (Learning 2; Reading 3; Writing 3; Oral Communication 3; Numeracy 2)
For Advanced Diploma (Learning 3; Reading 4; Writing 4; Oral Communication 3; Numeracy 3)
For Graduate Diploma (Learning 3; Reading 4; Writing 4; Oral Communication 4; Numeracy 4)
Students are required to provide copies of certificates and transcripts
